    <briefdescription>
<para>Describes a compute function&apos;s description. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>localSize: Optional. Specifices the 3D size of the local thread grouping. Defaults to 0, meaning it is not set. When x &gt; 0, y and z must also be set &gt; 0. When localSize is set to &gt; 0, the following source is generated: GLSL: layout(local_size_x = localSize[0], local_size_y = localSize[1], local_size_z = localSize[2]) in; MSL: [[max_total_threads_per_threadgroup(localSize[0] * localSize[1] * localSize[w])]]  </para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>
